'''''Vuk''''' es una pinicla d'animacion proucia pola estudio ''Pannónia Filmstudio'' en 1981. 
La pinicla hue derigia por Attila Dargay i escritu por Attila Dargay, István Imre, i Tarbay Ede, basá nun libru omónimo espublicau en 1965 pol utol húngaro István Fekete (1900-1970).

La estória gira en tornu a el çorru Vuk. Hue comercialisu enos paisis nel [[luenga ingresa]] como ''The Little Fox'' (''El pequeñu çorru'') i en [[España]] como ''Vuk, un zorrito muy astuto'' (''Vuk, un çorritu mui astutu'').

==Argumentu==
La pinicla cunta la estória de un pequeñu çorru kit, Vuk (Vic en la version ingresa), que ventures away from his family's den i, upon his return, learns from el su uncle Karak that his entire family has been shot i killed por un hunter human. Karak then offers for Vuk to stay with him, and Karak continues to raise him.

As Vuk grows older, he develops much cunning and cleverness. Now a young adult fox, he finds a vixen, named Foxy, held captive in a cage on a human farm. He tricks the guard dogs and other animals, as well as the hunter himself, and eventually helps the vixen escape.

She joins Vuk and Karak in the woods, but Vuk's uncle is shot by humans during a hunt. Vuk swears revenge on the hunter and finally accomplishes it, playing many jokes on the hunter's stupid dogs and eventually on the man himself. At the end of the film, Vuk and his wife have cubs of their own.

